<h1>Problem 892 - 2020 BMO2, P3 of 4</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>A \(2019\times 2019\) square grid is made up of \(2019^2\) unit cells. Each cell is coloured either black or white. A colouring is called <i>balanced</i> if, within every square subgrid made up of \(k^2\) cells for \(1\le k\le 2019\), the number of black cells differs from the number of white cells by at most one. How many different balanced colourings are there?</p>
<p><i>(Two colourings are different if there is at least one cell which is black in exactly one of them.)</i></p>
